```python
print("\\x9b")
```

When executed, this will display the ASCII bell character (BEL) as a visual representation, usually seen as a sound alert or notification on some terminal emulators. However, remember that actual audible feedback might depend on your system settings and environment. Here's what running the above code snippet should output:

```

```

Note that the actual appearance of the BEL character can differ across various platforms and terminal environments. Some systems may show it graphically while others may produce a sound alert.
